For the last two days I have been working on a new mural in my studio to test out @protapes masking tape. I have been wanting to use their masking tape for the last few years so it was awesome receiving a few sample rolls directly from them.
I want to start off by saying I highly recommend their tape. It’s been an incredible experience trying out their product for this mural and it exceeded my expectations.
Review:
The tape has a perfect amount of adhesion that won’t damage your walls but is strong enough to not fall off when creating intrigued designs. With most of the work I create, I have to continuously remove and reapply the tape on the wall to get perfect straight lines. Most tapes after executing this process, will lose its adhesion, and not stick properly. @protapes did not have that issue.
Another great thing about this tape is that it is not thick and it is easy to rip which is something I look for in a roll of tape because if its too thick or too hard to cut it could start cutting your fingers if used for a long period of time.

I do not have any cons for this masking tape. I love this tape!

In the next few days I will be testing out how well the masking tape performs when its painted over.

Thank you @protapes for letting me try out your masking tape!
Everyone please go check out their account for all their products!
@protapes
